                content: "This unit has covered some of the most sophisticated concepts in competitive debate: theory arguments built on interpretations and violations, economic reasoning, framework strategy, social issue navigation, value premises and criteria, and abstract concept argumentation. This review lesson consolidates everything and helps you see how these concepts interconnect.\n\nThese aren't isolated skills—they work together. Your framework determines how theory arguments are evaluated. Your approach to abstract concepts shapes how you construct value premises. Your evidence standards for economic debates apply equally to social issue debates. The strongest debaters integrate all these skills seamlessly, drawing on the right tool at the right moment.\n\nLet's walk through the major concepts, test your understanding, and connect the dots between everything you've learned.",
